candidates.title: Dvs fixes
candidates.body: Addresses #100 and fixes a number of bugs, but removes live conversion display. Once #95 is completed, can restore that functionality by adding this tool to adder-viz.

candidates.title: Macroize D_SHIFT arrays
candidates.body: I tried to find a way to do this in vanilla Rust, but Rust macros are pretty horrid, and it doesn't seem possible without something really hacky. I spent a lot of trying to make it work, but it seems too tricky. But with [a small crate](https://crates.io/crates/seq-macro), it's quite easy.

candidates.title: Perf4
candidates.body: Numerous optimizations for nearly double the transcoding speed at higher resolutions. The `Collapse` mode (now default) throws away redundant integrations for stable pixels. This has virtually no bearing on the quality, but dramatically increases the speed. It also makes the integration speed bounded, as we will only ever be performing up to two integrations at a time for each pixel. There's room to optimize this further.

Crf quality
candidates.body:
- Set all the ADDER parameters with a single, simple number
- An adjustable velocity parameter for the rate that the pixel sensitivity decreases
- Adjust the pixel sensitivities based on the proximity to detected features
- Add feature detection on the player side of `adder-viz`
- Fix the "fast" player mode
- Fix the file output in `adder-viz`

candidates.title: Corner detection
candidates.body:
Summary of changes:

- Implement feature detection algorithm on the instantaneous intensities of ADDER events
- Begin setting up lossy compression schemes and artithmetic encoding (this is experimental, set with the "compression" feature)
- Performance improvements
- Bug fixes in adder-viz
- More generic stream handling, to prepare for the future
